<h3 class="title">Fall Party For Paws 'A Festival of Food'</h3>
<div class="article">
 <p class="date">October 29, 2010</p>
  <p class="publication">The Herald-Chronicle</p>
  <div class="article-text">
   <p>The Fall Party for Paws in Sewanee will be a party and silent auction to benefit The Franklin County Humane Society and their shelter, Animal Harbor. It will be a festival of food generously donated by IvyWild Sewanee, Julia's Fine Foods, Lorena's, Modern Dave's Caf√©, Natural Bridge Events, Shenanigans, The Blue Chair and The Edgeworth Inn.</p>
   <p>The party will be held on Saturday, Nov. 20, 6-8 p.m. at The Sewanee Inn on University Avenue in Sewanee.</p>
   <p>Enjoy a feast of hors d'oeuvres and wines, beers, and mixed drinks; and the chance to bid on a selection of works by local artists and artisans, antiques, memorabilia, and other goods and services &ndash; and good company in a good cause.</p>
   <p>Tickets are $30 each or bring a friend and pay $50 for two. Tickets are available from Animal Care Center (967-6345), Town and Country Veterinary Hospital (967-3666), Bubbles and Bows (967-9397), Animal Harbor (962-4472), Carolyn Maher (962-9750), Andie Pate (308-8752), Cecelia Brodioi (967-2065), Sue Ridyard (sridyard@sewanee.edu or 598-9260), Pat Thompson (pthompson313@gmail.com or 598-1657), Susan Rupert (srupert@sewanee.edu or 967-8903).</p>
   <p>Proceeds from this event will be used by Animal Harbor to rescue, care for and rehome companion animals. </p>
